        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Full-fat ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "coconut milk",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "coconut milk",
                  "termId": "cmpbcymku0000osv4ue8dglgu"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " replaces most of the dairy milk in the sponge batter. The crumb comes out soft and slightly dense, with a clean coconut flavour that carries through the whole cake. Toast the desiccated coconut for the outside before the cake bakes. It cools while you bake. Press it on while the frosting is fresh and it sticks better.",
            "type": "text"
          }
