          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toast the coconut and bake the layers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread 150 g desiccated coconut on a baking tray and toast at 180°C for 5 to 7 minutes until pale gold, shaking the tray once. Watch it carefully; coconut turns from golden to brown very quickly. Allow to cool. Grease and line three 23 cm round tins. Beat the butter and sugar until pale and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, then fold in the flour, baking powder, and salt in alternation with the coconut milk. Fold in the 80 g untoasted desiccated coconut and vanilla. Divide between the tins and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool on racks.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add the sifted icing sugar in three additions and beat until thick and spreadable. Add the coconut extract. Refrigerate the frosting for 20 minutes if it feels too soft to spread. Stack the three layers with frosting between each, then coat the top and sides generously. While the frosting is still soft, press the toasted coconut all over the top and sides with clean hands, patting it in so it adheres.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
